Title: A non-Abelian Chern-Simons term for non-BPS D-branes
Authors: Bert Janssen, Patrick Meessen
Comments: 8 pages, contribution to the proceedings of the IVth annual TMR
  conference inParis (7-13 sept 2000); JHEP-style
Report-no: IFT-UAM/CSIC-00-26
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B526 (2002) 144-148
\\
  We propose a Chern-Simons term for N coinciding non-BPS D-branes. Demanding
full U(N) invariance and compatibility with T-duality, it is shown that it is
necessary to introduce new interaction terms, through which the non-BPS
D-branes couple to all p-form RR fields.
